-- India's Reliance Industries' shares gain 2.38 pct at pre-open on better earnings
-- By Indulal PM
-- Sun Jul 20, 2014 11:43PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, July 21 (Reuters) - Shares in India's Reliance Industries Ltd <RELI.NS> rose 2.38 percent to 1,000 rupees at pre-open, after its June-quarter earnings beat estimates.

The energy conglomerate on Saturday posted a net profit of 59.57 billion rupees ($988 million) in the quarter ended June, rising from 52.37 billion rupees a year earlier. Revenue rose 7.2 percent to 1.08 trillion rupees. [ID:nL4N0PU0BZ]